                {"src": "ellicott", "attr": "Ellicott's Commentary", "html": "<p>Rather, <em>as one who can deal gently with the ignorant and erring, because</em> he himself is compassed with infirmity. Either apathy or undue severity in regard to transgression would disqualify this representative of men to God. The language is so chosen as to exclude sinning with a high hand.</p>"},
