                {"src": "ellicott", "attr": "Ellicott's Commentary", "html": "<p>It is important to note that in passages of the Pentateuch where the high priest receives a special designation his title is almost always \"the anointed priest.\" Hence in the one designation, \"the Christ,\" are united the two testimonies of Scripture which follow: he is the Anointed King (Psalms 2:7), addressed by Jehovah as His Son; by the same Jehovah He is addressed as Priest for ever after the order of one who was both priest and king (Psalms 110:4).</p>"},
