                {"src": "clarke", "attr": "Adam Clarke's Commentary", "html": "<p>Προσαγορευθεὶς — being constituted, hailed, and acknowledged to be a high priest. In Hesychius we find προσαγορεύει translated ἀσπάζεται — hence we learn that one meaning of this word is to salute; as when a man was constituted or anointed king, those who accosted him would say, Hail king!</p>"},
